  "title": "Fix TUI scheduler log panel not showing new events",
  "agent_type": "developer",
  "description": "The _on_interval_tick method in app.py calls runtime_state.refresh() which appends new event lines (from _tail_event_log) to the scheduler_log Python list, but never writes them to the RichLog widget. The _append_log_line helper writes to the widget but is no longer called anywhere since reporter.py was deleted. Fix: in _on_interval_tick, capture len(scheduler_log) before refresh(), then call _append_log_line() for each new entry in scheduler_log[prev_len:] after refresh() returns.",
